visit_notes: Basal data not collected. Soil pit not described (revisit), pit samples and bulk density not collected. Subsites only.
location_description:
Karijini NP. Tom Price 52.7km East
Impact of introduced plants is low but there is some Malvastrum americanum and Bidens pilosa present. Grazing impact is absent, there is no evidence of grazing the plot is in a national park where introduced herbivores are largely excluded. There are some burnt Acacias in the plot, indicating a fire in the past 2-5 years.

description: Millstream Chichester National Park, adjacent to Water Corp facility. 97.2km south south east of Karratha
comments: Eucalyptus xerothermica and Corymbia hammersleyana low open woodland with mid stratum of Acacia bivenosa and lower stratum of Triodia wiseana on narrow limestone plain fronting the Millstream River. Long unburnt. Weeds and feral animal impact minimal. Site is homogenous, extends about 70m east, 100 south, 200m+ north and about 100 west. Old V-drain runs north to south through eastern half of plot. Eastern side of plot has more dense understorey especially Triodia.
location_description: Millstream NP adjacent Water Corp facility

description: Millstream Chichester National Park. 200m east of summit ( twin ) tanks. 21.5km SW of Mt Leal. 76km east north east of Pannawonica
comments:
Co-located site WA- Department of Parks and Wildlife PBS031/PW11.
Burnt in January 2015. Eucalyptus leucophloia regenerating both from the base and from unburnt branches. Some Coarse woody debris but not much. Surface strew mostly gravels with some outcrops of bedrock. Mudstone or sandstone. A couple of large termite mounds within the site. Homogeneity- site is homogenous. NW Corner borders track 10m NW of the site. 100m from site is homogenous otherwise. Site is concave- slopes up to the NE and SW corners with drainage depression through the middle. Minimal grazing. Introduced species minimal- Cenchrus ciliaris close by the site at large water tanks.
visit_notes: Too rocky to collect soil subsite samples.Metagenomics collected.
location_description: Millstream Chichester National Park. 200m east of summit ( twin ) tanks. 21.5km SW of Mt Leal. 76km east north east of Pannawonica

description: Millstream Reserve. 94.2km SE of Karratha. 94.8km Kanjenjie HS.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Landform element and pattern as previous. Site burnt 2 years ago by Parks, other side of road burnt last year. Site is homogenous and community extends 50m east, 200m North, 150 west, 100m south. Nearest infrastructure is the Roebourne-Wittenoom Rd 50m east of SE corner.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Co-located site with WA Department of Parks and Wildlife  PBS037/PW04
Plot is on a plain at the base of a series of low rises. Cobbles with some gravels to 20cm- minimal bare ground. Self-mulching soil. Lots of melon hole gilgai. Site slopes 2 degrees at 165. Homogeneity-  100m to where track is . 200m in all directions is the same community.
location_description:
Millstream Chichester National park. West Side of Road. 2.9 km north of Tom Price- Dampier Railway crossing on the Roeburn- Munjina Road., 4 km N of Barowabbahill, 69.4 km S of Roeburn
Introduced species minimal- Cucurbitaceae species possibly introduced but cover very low. Long unburnt but difficult to tell how long. Grazing effect is minimal.

description: Millstream Reserve. 94.2km SE of Karratha. 94.8km Kanjenjie HS.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Landform element and pattern as previous. Site burnt 2 years ago by Parks, other side of road burnt last year. Site is homogenous and community extends 50m east, 200m North, 150 west, 100m south. Nearest infrastructure is the Roebourne-Wittenoom Rd 50m east of SE corner.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Co-located site with WA Department of Parks and Wildlife  PBS037/PW04
Plot is on a plain at the base of a series of low rises. Cobbles with some gravels to 20cm- minimal bare ground. Self-mulching soil. Lots of melon hole gilgai. Site slopes 2 degrees at 165. Homogeneity-  100m to where track is . 200m in all directions is the same community.
visit_notes: No basal. Grassland.
location_description:
Millstream Reserve. 94.2km SE of Karratha. 94.8km Kanjenjie HS.
Introduced plant impact is low, Heliotropium sp., Cleome viscosa present. Grazing impact minimal, no evidence of grazing.

description: Millstream Chichester National Park. 200m upstream of concrete crossing on water corporation pipeline road over Fortescue river, southern bank. 22.7 km north north east of Mt Flora. 75.4 km east north east of Pannawonica
comments: Plot of the southern edge of the Fortescue River. Very gentle slope (1 degree) at 165 degrees. Very long unburnt. Grazing effect is minimal- some old cattle scats on track at northern edge of plot. Introduced species effect is low- some Passiflora foetida on Melaleucas but cover low at present. Some mixed gravels/ alluvial wash on northern edge with some small patches of calcrete along river levee- very little bare ground with most of the surface covered in dense leaf litter. Northern most transect heading west to east is along old track the follows the levee of the river. North east corner drops down very steep bank which was difficult to access so corner marked approx. 3m south on the top of the levee. Transects not affected.
visit_notes: Site contains deep litter of flood debris.
location_description: Millstream Chichester National Park. 200m upstream of concrete crossing on water corporation pipeline road over Fortescue river, southerrn bank. 22.7 km north north east of Mt Flora. 75.4 km east north east of Pannawonica

description: Millstream Chichester National Park, 3.3km north west of Ranger Station. 94.3km south south east of Karratha
comments: Undulating plot in complex of low rises with general slope to the south 6 degrees but steeper to the north of the site.  Very little bare ground- mostly covered by sandstone / mudstone mixed gravels with some outcrop in the creek through the middle of the site. Homogeneity- plot is homogenous- SW and NW corners are 20m from road ( Site is encircled on 3 sides by the road). Grazing effect is minimal. Long unburnt- mature clumps of Triodia forming hummocks and no scarring on Eucalyptus leucophloia. Introduced species effect minimal.
visit_notes: Site too rocky for soil pit, soil subsite and Metagenomic collection.
location_description: Millstream Chichester National Park

description: Adjacent Millstream National Park. West side of road. 18.9km west of junction with main Millstream Chichester National Park entry road on Millstream- Pannawonica road. 10.6km nnw of Mt Flora, 66.6 km ESE of Pannawonica
comments: Flat plot on sheet flood fan. Very long unburnt- Triodia to 1m high with dense clumps through the site. Grazing effect is low- some cattle pads and fresh scats through the site. Introduced species effect is low. Some very fine gravels with larger pieces to 2cms.
location_description: Adjacent to Millstream National Park. West side of road. 18.9km west of junction with main Millstream Chichester National Park entry road on Millstream- Pannawonica road. 10.6km nnw of Mt Flora, 66.6 km ESE of Pannawonica

description: Coolawanyah Station, 11.4 of Tambrey Station hms ruins, 3.4km ENE of Saddle Hill, 91.5km NW of Wittenoom
comments: Alluvial plain. Very long unburnt but difficult to tell exactly how long. Grazing effect is moderate- some cattle but not heavily grazed. Introduced species effect is minimal. Predominantly mudstone but some ironstone and quartz gravels and larger cobbles to 20cms. Homogeneity- SW corner is 20m from track. Community is consistent to 175m beyond the plot
location_description: Coolawanyah Station, 3.4km ENE of Saddle Hill, 91.5km NW of Wittenoom

description: Coolawanyah station. 1.7 km north north west of forest well. 8.1km south south east of homestead. 91km north of Tom Price
comments: Flat plot in a drainage depression on a broad alluvial floodplain. Very gentle slope to NW corner. Some isolated patches of  gravels of limestone origin. Grazing effect is low- some cattle present but grass cover intact. Introduced species effect is low- some Cenchrus ciliaris and Malvastrum americanum present.
location_description: Coolawonya station. 1.7 km north north west of forest well. 8.1km south south east of homestead. 91km north of Tom Price

description: Mt Florence Station. 14.2km south east of homestead. 56km north west of Wittenoom
comments: Upper slopes of sheet-flood fan; distal colluvium. Lots of gravel wash of ironstone, quartz and mudstone. Grazing effect is low. Introduced species effect is low. Long unburnt- no scarring on trees and few dead trees. NW corner is 15m from the road and 10m from grader bank. Broader community continues 80m from the centre of the site.
location_description: Mt Florence Station. 14.2km south east of homestead. 56km north west of Wittenoom

description: Mt Florence Station, 18km SE of homestead. West side of Road, 700m south of Hooley Creek crossing on Munjina- Roebourne Road. 52km NW of Wittenoom
comments: Site is flat with some minor undulations where water would pool. Alluvial plain. Grazing effect is low. Long Unburnt- very sparse ground cover. Introduced species effect is low- Cenchrus ciliaris present but cover low. Surface strew is metamorphosed rock mixed. Mostly gravels with the odd larger cobble. Very little bare ground- mostly covered by gravel pavement.
location_description: Mt Florence Station, 18km SE of homestead. WestSide of Road, 700m south of Hooley Creek crossing on Munjina- Roeburn Road. 52km NW of Wittenoom

description: Karajini National Park. 15km south west of Ranger Station. 54.7km east north east of Tom Price.Corresponds to WA Survey plot TCMBE-04 PBS-244
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Landform element:Hill slope
pattern:low hills
slope: 3-5% heading up to the northing edge
Lithology:
Site covered in Pilbara Iron-stone gravel with quartzite sizes are up to (3-10cm);  no outcrop located in the site . The site is covered in 100% of the ironstone and quartzite gravel.

Homogenous:
Confined to the plot, south edge turns into a mallee wood land.
western edge: same community (up to 200m) then turns into a mallee shrub land instead
north: same communities
east: same communities
nearest infrastructure : 50 south west corner the dirt road that was travelled on to get into the site.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Plot is among Low Hills on a hill Footslope. Gentle slope 5 degrees through the site 180 degrees. Metamorphosed rock. Gravel consistent through the site. Ant mounds only occurring on bare ground. Substrate count for gravel in point intercept higher at this site due to sparser cover in Triodia. No Outcrop. Corresponds to WA Survey plot TCMBE-04 PBS-244
location_description: Karajini National Park. 15km south west of Ranger Station. 54.7km east north east of Tom Price.Corresponds to WA Survey plot TCMBE-04 PBS-244.

description: Karajini National Park. 16.7km west south west of Ranger station.52.8km east north east of Tom Price
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Landform: Top of hillslope, low mountain. Slope is from south to north, 10 degrees from western edge to 15 degrees on eastern edge. Lithology: most of the site has hard ironstone gravel (3-6cm) with some larger rocks. 90% cover except for outcropping rock, is 10-15% of site. Depth of gravel is only a few centimetres before hitting bedrock. Homogeneity: top of hill limits extent. Northern side extends approx. 20m beyond plot before sharp drop-off / cliff. Similar for western edge, where community extends for 30-40m before slope drops away sharply. Eastern and southern edges the community extends down a gentle slope 100m before turning into a denser shrubland. Nearest infrastructure: very small track approximately 600m south of the SE corner.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Hill slope on range of low hills. Very little bare ground- lots of sandstone  gravel with larger rocks and outcrop.  Sloping site to 20 degrees to the SE. Slope somewhat uneven- some drainage gully’s through the site.
visit_notes: Too rocky for soil pit analysis and collection of subsite samples.
location_description: Karajini National Park. 16.7km west south west of Ranger station. 52.8km east north east of Tom Price.

description: Karijini National Park. 69km from Wittenoom.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Element is a low rise, pattern is a plain. There is some quartz and ironstone gravel (1-5cm) scattered throughout the plot. The site is homogenous and the community extends 200m in all directions. The nearest infrastructure is the access track 10m from the SE corner. There are two tracks going through the western side of the plot, running in a north-northwest direction and creating a clear vegetation disturbance. 
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Flat plot on an alluvial plain. An old track runs through the site at the SW corner passing out of the site on the southern edge. Homogeneity- track in site. Beyond the site community continues 100m from the centre of the site. Minimal surface strew- very scattered mudstone gravels in isolated patches.
location_description:
Karajini National Park. 24.2km south west of Ranger Station. 45.2km east north east of Tom Price.
Grazing effect is low- some evidence of cattle but effect is low. Introduced species minimal.

description: Hamersley Station. 45.4km south east of homestead. 18km north east of Tom Price. 12/05/2025 Unallocated Crown Land proposed for conservation - Ex-Hammersley Station
comments: Corresponds to WA biological survey plot TCMBE-10 PBS-274. Flat site on a footslope at the base of a range of low hills. Grazing effect is minimal. Introduced plant effect is minimal. Fire history difficult to tell- regenerating shrubland to the south  and west of the plot. 5 years since last fire. Homogeneity- 100m to nearest road however 40m past the western edge the community grades in an Acacia aneura shrubland. Surface strew of mudstone cobbles and boulders.
location_description: Hamersley Station. 45.4km south east of homestead. 18km north east of Tom Price

description: Karijini National Park. 24.5km south west of Ranger Station. 49.5km east south east of Tom Price
comments: Plot is in a stream channel on a braided alluvial plain. Grazing effect is low. Plot is flat broadly but undulating in places where creek channels flow through the plot.  Introduced species effect is high with Cenchrus setiger dominating the ground stratum and Sigesbeckia orientalis and Bidens bipinnata also common through the site. Most of the site has minimal surface strew but a creek channel through the middle of the site has alluvial gravel wash. Very long unburnt - no scarring on Eucalyptus victrix and Acacia sp.
visit_notes:
Basal wedge has counts for Eucalyptus camaldulensis and Eucalyptus victrix combined.
Pit in NW corner. Subsites 1 - 5 in NE corner. Very loose sand underlain with large rocks and gravel. Mudstone, Quartz and other coarse fragments found throughout pit and site.Couldn't determine colour, as there were too many particles of differing colours to make a determination.
location_description: Karajini National Park. 24.5km south west of Ranger Station. 49.5km east south east of Tom Price

description: Mulga Downs. Wittennoom 38km NE.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Community is confined to plot. Nearest infrastructure is railway access road 80m west of SW corner. Access to the site via side road 400m south of site and follow old grader track up ridge.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Plot on crest of hill in band of low hills. Moderate slope of 2 degrees though site- steeper through the eastern edge in a drainage gully. Very little bare ground- mostly covered by sandstone gravel and bedrock. Plot is sandwiched between two railway lines. Homogeneity- plot is contained- SW corner community begins to drop off down the hill towards a road.
visit_notes: Rocky nature of site prohibited the collection of Pit,Metagenomic and Subsite soil samples.
location_description:
Mulga Downs Station. 57.3km east south east of homestead. 43.8 km north east of Auski roadhouse.
Long unburnt- vegetation thicker in drainage line along running north to south along eastern edge. Minimal introduced plant species. Minimal grazing effect.

description: Mulga Downs. 1.3k  ESE of Mulga Downs outcamp.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Landform element: plain, low hills. Lithology: no surface strew, all dirt and grass, no outcrop. Nearest infrastructure is an access track running parallel to the northern side of the plot, which approximately 20m north of the NW corner. Train track approximately 2.4km east of the north east corner.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Flat site on the flood plain of the river. Homogeneity- NE corner is 20m from a track. 85m from centre is same community. Minimal surface strew and outcrop.

description: Mulga Downs. 4.3km NEof Mulga Downs Outcamp.
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
The landform element is a plain and the pattern is low hills. There is a slight slope (1) to the south-east. Ironstone and quartzite surface strew ranging between 10-20mm is present across the plot with few bare patches.The site is homogenous and the community extends 70m south, 60m west, 70m north, and 100m east from the centre picket. The nearest infrastructure is the access track 20 m went of the northwest corner.

-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Flat site on an alluvial fan on outer reaches of river floodplain. Undulating very slightly from east to west along a shallow drainage line. Lots of gravel through the site with patches of bare ground. Homogeneity- NE is 10m from track.
location_description:
Mulga Downs Station. 60.3km south east of Homestead. 34.4km north east of Auski Roadhouse.
Grazing effect is low- some evidence of cattle- scats and tracks. Introduced species effect is low- some Malvastrum americanum present. Long unburnt given age of Acacia xiphophylla and amount of grass cover. Some very old dead trees.

comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------

location_description:
Mulga Downs. 4.3km NEof Mulga Downs Outcamp.
Introduced plant impact is minimal, there is some Malvastrum americanum and one Cenchrus ciliaris individual was found. Grazing impact is high, most of the grasses and forbs have been grazed to a uniform height. Evidence of cattle and macropod grazers in the plot include many pads and scats. There are many younger Acacia xiphophylla seedlings emerging, as well as various shrub species recruiting. There is evidence of past fire in the plot, possibly more than 10 years ago.

description: Millstream Chichester National Park, 5.6km east south east of Ranger Station. 101 km south south east of Karratha
comments: Plot is on the slope of a  low rise. Plot has been burnt within last 2-3 years but patchy with some more mature spinifex within the site. A few very flat limestone outcrops but extensive limestone gravel pavement. Larger section of limestone outcrop to the north of the site. Some patches of cryptogam- very little bare ground. Gentle 2 degree slope to the south west. Homogeneity:  community extends 40m beyond the plot as far as track. Introduced plant species effect is minimal. Minimal grazing
location_description: Millstream Chichester National Park, 5.6km east south east of Ranger Station. 101 km south south east of Karratha

description: Millstream-Chichester National Park. 4.9km south east of Ranger Station. 100km south south east of Karratha.
comments: Plot on Alluvial plain- quite soft and spongy underfoot. More dense on the edges of the site. Extensive gravel pavements through the middle of the site. Mostly limestone surface strew with some ironstone mixed through. Long unburnt. Introduced plant effect is low- some Cenchrus ciliaris  in drainage line on the western edge of the site. Grazing effect is moderate. Digging possibly from pigs but more likely cattle. Camels also likely present- browse line on the Acacia xiphophylla. Drainage line running from north to south through the site- possibly a very old track or natural drainage line. Homogeneity- Vegetation community is confined to the plot but difficult to tell beyond the plot as vegetation is quite thick in places. South west corner is 10m from park access track which runs away from the plot in a north westerly direction.
location_description: Millstream-Chichester National Park. 4.9km south east of Ranger Station. 100km south south east of Karratha.

description: Millstream-Chichester National Park, 2.8km north east of ranger station. 97km south south east of Karratha.
comments: Floodout among low hills. Site is flat with some undulations and a drainage line that runs from the north west corner to the south east corner. Mixed surface strew of limestone and alluvial wash. Lots of bare ground. Grazing effect is low- cattle present. Long unburnt- but isolated scarring on Eucalyptus victrix possibly from lightning strike. Triodia forming tall hummocks. North of track is a much older stand of Triodia. Introduced plant effect is low- some clumps of Cenchrus ciliaris and Malvastrum americanum. Passiflora foetida also present but cover very low. Homogeneity- north west corner is 30m from track. Community extends 100m from centre of the site in all directions.
location_description: Millstream-Chichester National Park, 2.8km north east of ranger station. 97km south south east of Karratha.

comments:

Nearest infrastructure is access track 20m west of NW corner. Plot is homogenous and community extends, 100m south, north, east and 70m west.
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Plot is flat on a floodplain. Ironstone gravels at the surface, limestone below the surface with occasional larger limestone cobble at the surface. Homogeneity- plot is patchy at a subsite level with open patches of ground spread evenly through the site. North west corner is approximately 40m in from a station track that runs south westerly away from the plot.

Cattle present but grazing effect is low. Unburnt in last 2 years more like 5+ years. Low scarring on older mulga, none on younger trees. Introduced plant effect is low to moderate with Cenchrus ciliaris around the bases of trees.

Sheet flood fan or colluvial foot slope. Ironstone gravels through the site. Some fine gravels bordering on bare ground to larger gravels up to 2cms. Acacia aptaneura occurring in groves through the site.

description: 8.8km east south east of Newman, 10.9km west north west of Newman post office. 11.2km north west of Newman.
comments: Flat plot on sheet flood outwash fan. Half degree slope to the south. Minimal surface strew- mostly ironstone gravels with some quartz. Homogeneity- plot sits on the northern end of broad alluvial plain . 20m north east of plot is creek line. Community extends 60m to the south 200m east and west. North east corner is 15m from access track. Minimal grazing. Introduced plant effect is low- one patch of Cenchrus and Malvastrum. Fire- difficult to tell. 3-4 years since last fire possibly longer- No clumps of dead grass in the ground layer.
visit_notes: Grassland, no LAI or Basal Area measurements.
location_description: 8.8km east south east of Newman, 10.9km west north west of Newman post office. 11.2km north west of Newman.

description: North side of Giles Point Road at a point 8.4km south of great northern highway, 16km north east of Giles point. 53.1km north west of Newman.
comments: Colluvial footslope. 12 degree slope at 180 degrees at its steepest but levels out on northern and southern edges. Surface strew is a mix of Ironstone cobbles and gravels with some boulders. Some Ironstone outcrops. Homogeneity- community is contained to the site. Slope ends 10m from the bottom of the plot where it grades into more open Acacia incurvaneura. 20m from Counts Point road on the southern edge. Long unburnt- no scarring but tree on north edge has been hit by lighting- tree is alive but has burnt branches. Introduced plant species effect minimal. Minimal grazing- only Euros and kangaroos.
location_description: North side of Giles Point Track at a point 8.4km south of great northern highway, 16km north east of Giles point. 53.1km north west of Newman.

description: East of Giles Point Road, 8.4km south of Great Northern Highway, 10.9km north east of Giles Point., 54km north west of Newman.
comments: Flat plot on Alluvial fan. Lots of Ironstone gravel with patches of bare ground. Long unburnt- very sparse cover. Introduced plant species effect is minimal. Grazing effect is minimal. Homogeneity- community is confined to the plot. 10m to a small track. 30m north west of the plot is more major track.
visit_notes: Mulga species combined for basal wedge.
location_description: East of Giles Point track. 8.4km south of Great Northern Highway, 10.9km north east of Giles Point , 54km north west of Newman.

description: East side of Giles Point Road. 100m off track at point 13.4km south of Great Northern Highway, 6.1km north east of Giles Point. 56.4km north west of Newman.
comments: Alluvial plain on valley flat. Previously an open forest but has been burnt so most of the Acacia incurvaneura trees are dead. Grazing effect is low. Introduced species effect is low- Cenchrus ciliaris present. Has been burnt since initial visit 5+ years- hot fire. Minimal surface strew- some scattered flecks of Ironstone. Some very old overgrown shot lines? through the site running roughly East North East through the plot and continues over the main track to the west of the site.  One large old pile from bulldozer/grader. Homogeneity- beyond plot difficult to tell due to thickness of veg. Plot is homogenous. 100m from nearest used track.
location_description: East side of Giles Point track. 100m off track at point 13.4km south of Great Northern Highway, 6.1km north east of Giles Point. 56.4km north west of Newman.

description: 7.3km north north east of Innawally Pool on Jimblebar Creek, 12.3km north east of Wheelarra Hill. 50.2km east north east of Newman.
comments: Flat plot on sandplain. Very little surface strew but some ironstone gravels to small cobbles in a patch in the North East corner. Some hardened/ clumped sand grains also but only marginally bigger than bare substrate.  Long unburnt, burnt closer to the track on the southern edge of the site. Introduced plant effect minimal. Grazing effect is minimal- some cattle present in area. Homogeneity- community continues 100m in all directions beyond the plot. South west corner is 15m from mine access track. Some new tracks going in to the north of the site for drilling campaign.
location_description: 7.3km north north east of Innawally Pool on Jimblebar Creek, 12.3km north east of Wheelarra Hill. 50.2km east north east of Newman.

description: South side of Track, 3.6km east of Caramulla Creek on track to Newman from Jigalong via Jimblebar mine, 22.3km east of Wheelarra Hill. 62.8km east of Newman.
comments: Flat plot on a sandplain. Grazing effect is low- camel tracks through the site. Introduced plant effect is low- Cenchrus ciliaris around the base of the Corymbia hamersleyana. Fire- moderately long unburnt. Triodia is quite old. No scarring on Corymbia. Minimal surface strew. Some coarser sands but not separated as gravel. Homogeneity- plot sites within extensive Corymbia/Triodia community- homogenous 100m from the edge of the plot in all directions. North east corner is 60m from narrow access track.
location_description: South side of Track, 3.6km east of Caramulla Creek on track to Newman from Jigalong via Jimblebar mine, 22.3km east of Wheelarra Hil. 62.8km east of Newman.

description: Lowlands Conservation Reserve. 1km south south east of Lowlands homestead, 7.4km west north west of Serpentine township.
comments: Bassendean dune above surrounding alluvial plains. Plot is flat with some very minor undulations. Very long unburnt- at least 50 years since last fire but one very old burnt tree in the site possibly from a lightning strike. Plot sits just outside the edge of current Phytophthora dieback front.   Introduced plant effect is moderate- Hypochaeris glabra is a dominant in the ground stratum but cover of other introduced species- Ursinia anthemoides subsp. anthemoides,  Sonchus oleraceus, Zantedeschia aethiopica and others is low. Grazing effect is moderate- kangaroos principally- unstocked historically and at time of visit. No surface strew. Much leaf litter through the site. Homogeneity- community is contained to plot due to the effects of dieback just beyond eastern edge of the plot although it sits in a consistent patch of Banksia woodland. 30 east of the site is an access track.
visit_notes: Banksia attenuata and Banksia menziesii were combined for basal wedge under Banksia attenuata.
location_description: Lowlands Conservation Reserve, 1km south south east of Lowlands homestead. 7.4km west north west of Serpentine township.

description: Lowlands Nature Reserve. 400m north east of Lowlands homestead, 7.3km north west of Serpentine township.
comments: Bassendean dune above surrounding alluvial plains. Very long unburnt- 50+ years. One or two very old burnt trees. Introduced plant species effect is low- Hypochaeris glabra present but cover low. Some other species including Zantedeschia aethiopica, Briza maxima and Romulea rosea var. australis but cover minimal. Grazing- some impact from kangaroos but not formally grazed. Homogeneity- difficult to tell exactly beyond plot due to thickness of vegetation but plot is homogenous. Track running north south to the west of the site. North west corner is about 20m in from cleared fire break along track edge.
visit_notes: Banksia attenuata and Banksia menziesii were combined for basal wedge under Banksia attenuata.
location_description: Lowlands Conservation Reserve, 400m north east of Lowlands homestead. 7.3km north west of Serpentine township.

description: Lowlands Nature Reserve. 1km east south east of Lowlands homestead, 6.7km north west of Serpentine township.
comments: Swamp/Floodout of Serpentine River. South west and south east corners are on the edge of the main river channel. River arcs away from the plot along southern boundary. Plot is more or less flat but slopping gently at the northern edge towards the track. A floodout channel comes into the plot at the south east corner. Minimal surface strew- dense leaf litter covers most of the plot.  Plot is not formally grazed but kangaroos present. Also possible diggings from Bandicoots. Very long unburnt- 50+ years. Introduced plant effect is high- ground story is dominated by introduced forbs and grasses, particularly Oxalis spp.   Homogeneity- Vegetation community is more or less confined to the plot. North east corner is just intersected by old track/turn around area. Very old overgrown track ( likely old access road) runs east to west though the site at the 70m mark. North of the plot is the main east west access track and north of this is Banksia woodlands.
location_description: Lowlands, River

description: Yeal Nature Reserve. 18.4km west south west of Gingin.
comments: Dune Swale in low dunefield. Unburnt for at least 30 years. More recent fire to the south of the site. Introduced plant effect is minimal. Grazing pressure is low at time of visit. Plot is 100 north of flux tower/park access track.

description: Parrys Lagoon Conservation Reserve. 2.3km south east of the Grotto. 30km south east of Wyndham
comments:
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments start --------------
Parry Lagoons Nature Reserve. Slope and aspect unchanged since last visit. A lot of sandstone strew cobble up to boulders some gravel. 
-------------- new visit physicalStatusComments end ---------------
Plot is on the foothills of a range low hills. 9 degree slope- steeper up towards the south west corner- peters out towards the north east corner. Fire- some dead Erythrophleum regenerating from the base. Probably burnt in last 2 years. Sandstone surface strew with some chert- mostly cobbles bigger than 50m. To the north of the site is a gully dominated by annual Sorghum spp. 270m from Wyndham road.

description: Edel Land National Park. 150m south of western most point sign, 45km south west of Denham.
comments: Dune slope dropping down to cliffs on western edge. 6 degree slope to the west. Some very low limestone outcrops and some limestone cobbles but mostly covered by sand. Long unburnt. Not grazed but possibly some rabbits. Introduced plant effect is low but Senecio may be a weed- check Ids and inform Rangers.  Plot is homogenous- a little bit rockier on western edge. Extensive community along dune slope to the south. To the north is turnaround area for steep point car park. North east corner is about 15m from track moving away to the north west corner which is about 35m south of turnaround area.
visit_notes: no basal - not enough canopy
location_description: Edel Land National Park, 150m south of western most point sign. 45km south west of Denham

description: Edel Land National Park. 11.9km south west of ranger station, 43.4km south west of Denham.
comments: The site is situated on a dune slope in a dune field with a 7 degree slope tending towards the west. There is a small amount of limestone outcropping in the north west corner and some limestone gravel as well. The vegetation community is homogenous although does get thinner towards the base of the sand dune (western edge) but the vegetation species are the same. The community extends a few 100ms to the north and ~100m to the east and stops at a track to south. To the west, the community transitions in the dune swale to become a dense shrubland with a similar species composition with the addition of a few other Acacia species. The nearest infrastructure is the Shark Bay 4WD track which is 20m from the south west corner. There is also a disused 4WD track just outside the western edge of plot. In terms of grazing, the impact is low with evidence of rabbits, macropods and emus and the impact of introduced plants is minimal. The site is also long unburnt.
location_description: Edel Land National Park, 11.9km south west of Ranger Station. 43.4km south west of Denham

description: Edel Land National Park. 14.4km south east of Shark Bay Ranger Station, 43.5 south west of Denham.
comments: Dune slope rising up to crest of the dune that overlooks bay. Avg 5-6 degree slope to the west but flattens out at the top. No surface strew. Long unburnt but some dead trees. Grazing effect is low- some rabbits and goats. Lysimachia and Hypochaeris but cover is quite low. Homogeneity- 75m from centre of the plot is same community- more or less confined to the plot but continues along dune slope to the north and south. South west corner is 50m in from Steep Point access track.
location_description: Edel Land National Park 43.5 SW, Denham, 14.4 SE Shark Bay Ranger Station

description: Edel Land National Park. 12.4km south east of ranger station, 43.5km south west of Denham.
comments: The site is a perched swamp situated in the swale of a dunefield. There is a small amount of cobble-sized limestone fragments as well as a little bit of sandstone gravel. The swamp is relatively flat but drains to the north. The site is homogenous and the community extends 60m from centre of the plot to west, about 40-15m to the south where it is stopped by a road, it finishes along the eastern edge of plot and extends 80m to north but transitions to more of a Melaleuca dominated shrubland. The nearest infrastructure is the main 4WD track through the park and it is about 10-15m to the south from the south west corner. The site is long unburnt and the impact of grazing is low with only evidence of macropod scats and pads. The impact of introduced weeds is also minimal.
location_description: Edel Land National Park, 12.4km south east of Ranger Station. 43.5km south west of Denham

description: Edel Land National Park. 25.6km south east of ranger station, 56.3km south west of Denham.
comments: Plots is a dune slope in a dune field with 5 degree slope that peters out on the eastern edge. Slope is to the east. No surface strew- very sandy. Long unburnt- lots of old dead growth in the shrub layer but no evidence of recent fire. Grazing effect is minimal- kangaroos possibly goats too but in low numbers. Plot is homogenous- community extends across the track and for 200m+ to the south. Track is 10m in from the eastern edge.
location_description: Edel Land National Park, 25.6km south east of Ranger Station. 56.3km south west of Denham

description: Charles Darwin Reserve. 15.8km north north east of homestead, 98km north north east of Dalwallinu.
comments: Landform element and pattern, hill slope in rises. Surface strew is pebble size ironstone, quartzite and granite. Introduced species impact low. Grazing impact is low, kangaroos present. Nearest infrastructure is the station access track 20m North of NE corner. Site is long unburnt, a lot of fall coarse woody debris but no fire scarring. Site is homogenous. Extends 150m East, South and North 60m. Slight slope to North East ~1 degree, with a drainage line down the centre of site.
location_description: Charles Darwin Reserve, 15.8km north north east of Homestead. 98km north north east of DALWALLINU

description: Charles Darwin Reserve. 8.9km north of homestead, 97.3km west south west of Morawa.
comments: The site is a lunette with the broader landscape being an alluvial plain. No surface strew or outcrop apparent, however, there is a handful of patches of limestone gravel. The site is homogenous and the community extends 60m from the centre of the plot to the south, 150m to the east, 70m to the west and 30-40m to the north. The community transitions to a more open chenopod shrubland to the east and a sandy samphire shrubland to the south. The nearest infrastructure is the access track 30-40m north of north west corner. A Rangelands Plot is also located just to west of plot. The site is long unburnt with no evidence of previous fire and a fair amount of coarse woody debris. The impact of introduced plants is low to moderate with a few weed species present e.g. Sisymbrium. The impact of grazing is also low with rabbit and macropod scats observed.
location_description: Charles Darwin Reserve, 8.9km north of homestead.  97.3km west south west of Morowa

description: Charles Darwin Reserve. 13.2km north east of homestead, 39.3km west north west of Mount Gibson.
comments: The site is a plain situated on a plain with no outcrop evident but with some fine gravel-sized ironstone surface strew scattered in patches across the plot.  The nearest infrastructure is an access track located 20m to the north west of the north west corner. The vegetation community is homogenous and extensive, continuing a few hundred metres in all directions. The site is long unburnt with no evidence of fire scarring on any of the trees. The impact of introduced plant species is minimal as is the impact of grazing, with only a few kangaroo scats present.
location_description:
Charles Darwin NR Homestead, 13.2km
Mount Gibson, 39.3km WNW
